The paper deals with the algorithmic study of demand-aware networks (DANs) designs, which are networks that can be reconfigured depending on the workload. This topic is closely related to network optimization and design, which falls under the category of computer science and networking (cs.NE). The paper also involves the design of bounded-degree networks, which is a topic in graph theory and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions connections to information theory (cs.IT), as well as classic combinatorial problems (cs.SI) and datacenter interconnects (cs.DC).
